DEUTSCHMASCHINE PRESENTS:

DE_VOSTOK

WATCH THE TRAILER NOW!

this css version based on the original 1.6 map from valve
redesigned and mapped by: uzy (sgill243@bellsouth.net) by order of: www.deutschmaschine.de (info@deutschmaschine.de)
mapname: de_vostok filesize: 14.5 (packed 5 MB) spawnpoints: 32 (config-files for 64 spawnpoints included!) bombsites: 2 (in front of the church and at the big statue) available weapons: standard
this download-package contains: - de_vostok.bsp - de_vostok.bsp.bz2 - trailer_vostok.wmv - 10 big screenshots - 27 thumbnails in 3 sizes (large, medium, small) - 64 spawnpoints-file for "stripper source" - 64 spawnpoints-file for "mani admin plugin" - 64 spawnpoints-file for "cssdm deathmatch" this map has 32 spawnpoints (16 x Terror, 16 x CT)but you´ll get everything you need to play de_vostok with up to 64 players, even with cssdm deathmatch. .nav, .txt and radar-overview-files are already embeded in the .bsp file.
WE SAY THANK YOU: to all deutschmaschine-testers. special thanks to duni, mete, brot and absinth for their special patience. and special, special thanks to Misses Uzy for not leaving him!
other maps from our mapper uzy you´ll find at: http://www.fpsbanana.com/members/subs/168576 you also should check out our download-section. from time to time we will release new maps there, f.e. the forthcoming map de_sunny, mapped by uzy. www.deutschmaschine.de
Happy Death! Panza

de_volunteer_beta


Theme:

A group of Terrorists is set to destroy some historical artifacts in a market, but volunteers to take out a disguised military factory exposed in a nearby location. Counter-Terrorists must prevent both targets being hit.

-------------

Hi all I'm new to mapping and this is just the second map I've created (may upload my 1st one later on).

I am aware the long corridors surrounding site B may put a few off, however they are intend to provide an alternative but 'lengthy' routes going around Bombsite B. I am not sure if I should place boxes / decorations along these hallways though.

Feedback and comments much appreciated. =)

_Please beware the elevator may not function properly yet._ (OLD - see below)

EDIT: _Also final version will be shipped with radar map and locations._ (OLD - see below)

UPDATE / EDIT (2011-05-01): Map is now shipped with everything (materials, overviews, nav locations) packed into the .bsp by PackBSP.

de_volunteer

Theme:

A group of Terrorists is set to destroy some historical artifacts in a market, but volunteers to take out a disguised military factory exposed in a nearby location. Counter-Terrorists must prevent both targets from being hit.

-------------

Hi all I'm new to mapping and this is just the second map I've created (may upload my 1st one later on).

I am aware the long corridors surrounding site B may put a few off, however they are intend to provide an alternative but 'lengthy' routes going around the bombsite.

The main difference between this and the beta's the lighting, and some alterations / extended parts.

Feedback and comments much appreciated. =)

DE_VOLID
Map made by: Solid

Bot support .nav file will be in the download!

de_volid is one of my first map creations in source. I've tried to make angles and team sides as balanced as I could with my limited knowledge. Hopefully everyone enjoys it!

If you do decide to play the map please give me feedback on how to improve angles, spawns or anything else really.

This is a map with a giant volcano in the middle and many lush plants around. And yo top it off with all the foliage around, fog will make your hiding spots even sneakier. I hope you all enjoy.

Features: 
-Bombsite on top of the smoky volcano
-Foggy weather

Install:
Extract the map file (de_volcano_gpk.bsp), and the navigation file to your Counter-Strike maps folder (Usually located here:C:\Program Files\steam\steamapps\***YOURNAMEHERE***\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps).

Author: GabrielPapaK

Time: 4 Hours

Hope you enjoy!

_aChangeLog.text: Fixed up the jank-ass area next to A
Planted some shrubs
Minor additions
Made the skybox HUG the map
Lots of fancy nodraw textures in areas where you'll never see
I didn't like the sand very much. It is now grass
Made some nice brick effects on various walls, windows and doors. Thoughts?
Shortened the house between River and Bombsite B
Removed the area behind TSpawn by extending TSpawn's room
Removed the wall between the eating area and the walkway behind Bombsite A
Added a ladder from the eating area to the balcony overlooking courtyard
Reversed the 'lobby' area
Instead of the broken hole in the wall between Crates and Courtyard, there are now two very nice holes in the wall.
Crates has been moved to the right side of the wall, so it's not effectively the same as Long Hall
There is now a slight gap in the wall blocking the walkway behind Bombsite A. There was something similar in a previous version, but I think it wasn't released
Changed the ramp next to Lobby and Long to be stairs
Made the eating area next to Bombsite A look so fuckin supreme
Clipped lots of stairs, may have missed a few
Rounded areas I wanted to be more rounder
Added a sewer from lobby to the area between TSpawn and the house, now referred to as River
Lots of inaccesible decorative areas, for no reason other than I like them :-)

De_Vine2 map by Slackiller

Map has HDR and LDR lighting.

Terroists: must find one of the 2 bomb sites and detonate the bomb,or
kill all the counter-terroists

Counter-Terroists: must stop the terrorists from blowing up the importants documents/computers or the loading dock on back of the main building.

I have recently fixed this awesome map because original version doesn't work on newer source engines anymore.

**Fixes/Tweaks**

- Added HDR
- Now 64 Spawn points instead of 24!
- Replaced missing textures and overlays with new ones
- Fixed foliage and vine lighting
- Removed fog which was causing weird lighting effects
- Removed unnecessary foliage fading
- Added entry to the balcony on 2nd floor
- Removed some unnecessary nodraw textures which were causing strange house transparency
- Fixed darkness in main hall caused by usage of hdr
- Added ladder from outside to "B" bombsite to improve gameplay/tactics
- Fixed trees' and 3DSkybox trees' gray textures. Now environment looks much more realistic

**Changes in 1.1**

- Restored some original textures
- Restored two ladders on the facade
- Added old, custom "nav" file for bots.
- Changed sprite textures. Now they look smoother.
- Generated cubemaps textures for shiny effect.
- Restored radar overview and txt file

FILENAME: de_villa_cocaina.bsp
FILESIZE: 10,2 MB
DATE RELEASED: 05.11.2006

CREDITS:
nearly everything - me
beta testing - Neo Nemesis
uploading - BigDog ;)

Introduction
Evertime when i was bored and had time (in the last months) I worked a little bit on this map.
The story may seems to be freaky, because this map was planned to be a HL² SP-series.

Story
With the intention to "clean" their small town from a group of cocaine dealers and consumers,
some residents, camouflaged as an anti terror unit, have confiscated 3 tonnes of columbian cocaine and charged it with atrazin.
They thought, no one would dare to take a step into this haunted villa.
The cocaine dealers, formally known as "Terrorists", have to burn the poisoned cocaine,before the insane residents sell it. "
This is my 3rd map :p... So download it and enjoy !!!
move the file in the folder cstrike\maps

The map is identical to that of CS 1.6, the map is held on the top of a building in construction in New York, it occurs on 2 stages, the terrorists starts on the first floors, the Anti-Terrorist with 2nd and the bomb is placed on one of the 2 site of the 2nd stage. 
The map is reproduced with identical, on the level structure only, of that of CS 1.6. The models were changed.

Have Fun!

A map i made for Counter-Strike: Source.

i'm going for a similar approach of 3kliksphilip when it comes to mapping. i make bombsites and spots one at a time and modify them.

talking about 3kliksphilip, this mid section is HEAVILY inspired by de_sparity as you can see in the video.

also if you go to my profile, you might see another map i made.

i will finish this map first as i think that map was not THAT good but will have  special place in my heart as it was the first map i ever made (for css atleast, i have other complete maps for cs 1.6 but chose not to submit them.).
